<TITLE> 6 more bodies found in Buriganga, death toll reaches 45 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 02 (bdnews24.com)Police retrieved six more dead bodies up to noon Sunday from the Buriganga, in the wake of Thursday's disastrous launch accident, pushing the death count to 45. Friends and relatives of the still missing passengers of ML Sourav-1 were seen crowding the Buriganga banks around the accident spot near the Buriganga Bridge-1, hoping against hopes to find the bodies of their loved ones. Syed Sajjad Selim, South Keraniganj police chief told bdnews24.com: "Police today (Sunday) have recovered the dead bodies of one female, three males and two children." The launch bound for Dohuri, Munshiganj, sank with about 150 passengers on board as a sand-carrying trawler rammed into it from behind. Till Friday, 39 bodies had been recovered. bdnews24.co
